The**Order Refunded**trigger activates a flow when an order is marked as refunded in the system.

<Note>
  **Note:** This Trigger is a part of
  [BigCommerce](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/6774740880153-Introduction-and-Installation-of-BigCommerce)
  Integration
</Note>

**Topics Covered:**

- [How to Configure Order Refunded Trigger](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/37780236376345-Order-Refunded#h_01J8HC1NV9SQSNHHHY2R836XGF)

- [Practical Example](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/37780236376345-Order-Refunded#h_01J8HDDRJPJ38772ETZP59RETE)

### How to Configure Order Refunded Trigger

- While creating the Trigger Based Flows select**Order Refunded**trigger.

![](./Order Refunded – Salesmate_files/mceclip0.png)

- When configuring the**Order Refunded**trigger, you'll need to complete the following steps:
  **\*Name:**Give the trigger a clear, descriptive title to easily identify its function.
  **\*Description:**Provide a concise explanation of the trigger's purpose within the flow.
  **\*Select Store:**Choose the relevant BigCommerce store where the order refund process is being tracked.
  **\*Contact:**Specify any conditions based on customer details.
  **\*BigCommerce:**Define specific order-related conditions, like refund amount, reason for the refund, or other criteria to refine when the trigger is activated.

- Once the configuration is completed, hit**Save**.

![](./Order Refunded – Salesmate_files/mceclip1.png)
